	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Oct 11th 7:41 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>311 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.66]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>While I can appreciate what Shrikke is saying, Im not sure that I agree.<br><br>There is such an immense time commitment needed in order to hit 60, I sure as heck wouldnt do anything to slow that down.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you can presently tank 10 mobs at once solo, fine, have fun and level as fast as you can.  People far too often discount the impact of leveling (i.e. quests, aa abilities, etc.).  Its probably the single most important thing you can accomplish.  You can learn on the fly as far as I would be concerned.<br><br>If you dislike non-linear things, then you are sure to dislike this:  your learning curve in this game sure as heck is NOT linear.  What you learn from 50-60 is tremendously different than what you learn from 1-50.  You're only lvl 24.  I wouldnt sweat it at all.<br><br>When you get 30+, then I would start focusing on grouping, especially in OT.  OT was where I really learned how to &quot;chain&quot; pull and that lesson will be carried right through to 50 (say in DL after OT).<br><br>Post 50, however, your pulling methods will generally be vastly different.  More often than not, you are staying with the group until the mob is finished (granted, there are exceptions; note the word generally).  The zones are generally more challenging, as well as the mobs.  You seldom chain pull anymore.<br><br>Also, you then learn the importance and value of both CLR and ESPECIALLY chanters.  I thought chanters were cute and all, but definitely not necessary pre-50.  Well, 50+, there are just some zones that you cant effectively survive without one.  You can, SOMETIMES, but it isnt easy.<br><br>The list goes on and on (split-pulling is something that you will focus more on 50+ also), so I wouldnt sweat it now at all.<br><br>As far as some of the other things mentioned:<br><br>1)  Shadow Stepping out of a fight.  The teleport is random and always seems to be a major pain in the butt to be consistently effective.  If you find success, have fun, but life changes at 30 with FD, so SS only really has value after that for PvP to me. <br><br>2)  Fearing an additional mob while fear-kiting another.  I would seldom ever recommend this, as this definitely has some risk associated with it.  I would never do this in a dungeon, as your feared mob will probably bring back friends.  In an open area, you may be able to get away with this, but I have seldom ever employed this strategy.  OOM, adds, and basically the pain associated with fighting / targeting two mobs makes this a high-risk tactic.<br><br>3)  Overpulling and dying to save the group.  Post 30, this is almost NA, as you have FD.  If you overpull, FD.  We arent mindless WAR now....  =)<br><br>I agree 100% with the grouping comment.  If you want to do some of the most exciting things in this game / get the best gear out there, etc., then you are going to need some friends to do that.<br><br>Luna<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
