	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>311 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.82]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>At the end of the day, fun is the name of the game and should be everyone's ultimate goal.&nbsp;&nbsp;That goes almost without saying.<br><br>Therefore, people can do what they want to when they play.  If they are having fun, no one can argue with that point.<br><br>In general, however, most people have a goal, which is probably ranked fairly high, to obtain a high level and / or get nice items.  That is the way the game is built and is one of the elements (albeit probably a strong one) that makes it so appealing to a lot of people.  This guy has a pretty decent twink.  That suggests to me that he wants to do more than solely shoot the crap with his buds in game.  I dont know for sure though.  That is just how it struck me.<br><br>If my statement above is true, I certainly would never ebay any character, to say nothing about a SK.  You have to learn how to play any character and an SK is typically viewed as a challenging class to play, as they are very self-sufficient class that can do a lot of things.<br><br>You said you would have him bank all his nice gear to, essentially, learn how to play his SK.  Im sorry, but I disagree.  The time committment is just too damn big for him not to get that experience (or &quot;tools&quot; as you put it) that he needs.  In other words, it isnt like with his present gear he is going to race to 60 without any problems.  It just doesnt work that way.  His present gear, especially when factoring in what his level will be as compared to the zones that he will be fighting in, will definitely give him substantially all the experience he needs.<br><br>Hell, you could put a lvl 30 SK in full SS armor and, while he may be leaps and bounds ahead of all the other SKs in, say, OT, he still will be learning his class and risking death.  Level caps make good sense in situations like these.<br><br>I also assumed that the smiley face =) following my derogatory comment about WAR demonstrated that I was kidding.  I do not distain WAR in any way, nor was I serious when calling them mindless.  /sigh<br><br>I also have some bad news for you and taking a SK to a raid.  We arent a extremely desired class and definitely are very expendible at raids.  About the only unique thing we bring to raids is an agro buff, which sure as hell doesnt make a monumental difference.  Furthermore, a lot of classes can do DPS equal to or greater than we can, so dont expect that the red carpet will be rolled out when heading to a raid.  Trust me, it pains me to say that, but its the truth.  I only wish Verant would give us SOMETHING unique to where raids leaders would say, &quot;Damn, I wish we had few SKs here.&quot;  At the moment, I can assure you that that is seldom, if ever, said at a raid.<br><br>Also, Im not sure that your analogy about getting 20 yrs of experience vs 20 yrs of the same experience holds water in the EQ world.  It just isnt possible to stay in the same zone doing the same thing over and over again and get to lvl 60.  <br><br>Further, with that analogy, you suggest that I believe that getting to lvl 60 is more important than experience.  That is absolutely, without question, an inaccurate assumption.  As stated above, you need to learn how to play your character and that only comes from playing him.  Your comment about banking all his gear suggests that he wouldnt get that experience.  I disagree.  He almost assuredly will, even with the gear.<br><br>Luna</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
